    <name>Assignment #3: Explore Research on SCL and Relate it to Math Instruction</name>
    <intro>&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 13px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.231;"&gt;Explore the research behind student-centered learning and motivation and consider how you can apply what you learn to math instruction. Spend more time learning about student-centered learning with these three sources:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A NCSALL Focus on Basics publication:&lt;em&gt;&lt;a title="new website - opens in new window - The First Three Weeks: A Critical Time for Motivation" href="http://www.ncsall.net/index.php@id=420.html" target="_blank"&gt;The First Three Weeks: A Critical Time for Motivation&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;, by B. Allan Quigley&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Selected Readings from Jobs for the Future publication: &lt;a title="pdf - opens in new window - Motivation, Engagement, and Student Voice" href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/Pages%2023-34%20from%20MotivationEngagementStudentVoice.pdf" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Motivation, Engagement, and Student Voice&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span color="#0000ff"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;(pages 23-34): &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;How Student Voice Can Elevate Motivation and Engagement&lt;/em&gt; (pages 23-29)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Why Student Voice is Student-Centered Learning&lt;/em&gt; (pages 30-32)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Conclusion&lt;/em&gt; (pages 33-34)  &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An excerpt from &lt;a title="PDF - opens in new window - More Complicated Than It Seems: A Review of Literature about Adult Numeracy Instruction" href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/Page%203-15%20from%20morecomp.pdf" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;i&gt;More Complicated Than It Seems: A Review of Literature about Adult Numeracy Instruction &lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;(pages 3-15), by Kate Nonesuch.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Write a one-page reflection of how you can put students at the center of math instruction and activities. (Click Add or Edit my submission)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
